        "id": 275346,
        "name": "Thomas Bohn",
        "username": "tehabe",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/tehabe/{size}/9333_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-09-14T07:40:11.311Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Partially not an issue, you can use a “create” icon, next to it a search icon and on the right side a combined thingy with “Chats”, “Stories”, and “Calls”. Five buttons on the bottom seems fine, no idea about six though, so no idea about the photo.</p>\n<p>For me personally, “create a new message” and “search” are the most important buttons. Stories are disabled and I go to “calls” mostly on accident. I understand the point of photo but I never used it.</p>",
