        "id": 279712,
        "name": "Rodrigo",
        "username": "rodrigo",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/rodrigo/{size}/47505_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-11-20T14:17:14.920Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I don’t think Signal (or any other apps) has to follow Messages lead in terms of UI/UX, but that search isn’t an expendable Liquid Glass button in the bottom row, like many apps are using, is a big miss in fitting in LG aesthetics, discoverability, and better usability.</p>\n<p>Since Signal’s LG implementation is a work in progress, I hope this change lands soon.</p>",
